  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: assurance overstatement)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below their required levels, the package declares assuranceLevel High and records an Accepted decision — constituting an assurance-level overstatement (COMPOUND-03). This is a synthetic adversarial sample.",
